description:
Basic Function: The Senior Accountant is the subject matter expert (SME) in Accounting (according to U.S. GAAP) within DCL, and owns and drives several important monthly processes: 

(i)	month-end close, consolidation and reporting of financial statements according to DCL Accounting Policies and U.S. GAAP;
(ii)	oversees (including quality control) downstream use of financial statements and supporting data in key Financial Planning & Analysis functions such as budgeting and ongoing monthly Budget-Vs.-Actual analysis;
(iii)	overseeing ongoing detailed analysis of cost structure (both direct and indirect), including reconciliation of vendor activities and invoices with DCL financial outcomes – to support operations leadership decisions around usage of vendors and their products and services;
(iv)	regular interactions with IT relating to configuration and reporting of data from Oracle JD Edwards EnterpriseOne to meet Finance and Accounting needs;
(v)	acting as a guide for quality control of upstream bookkeeping functions and controls, to help ensure downstream accuracy of financial statement and metrics outputs;
(vi)	support the CFO in ongoing budgeting and cost control initiatives involving other members of senior management; and,
(vii)	coordinate the provision of information to senior management and external CPAs for regular review.

Some management (including development) of junior team member(s) will be required, as there are 1-2 other Accounting positions directly reporting to the Senior Accountant. Other roles within the Accounting group report to the Accounting Manager. Day-to-day collaboration between the Senior Accounting, Accounting Manager and CFO are of critical importance, so the ability to communicate clearly is a must for this position. As DCL’s operations are distributed across four different regions nationally, the ability to support the business remotely via phone, Zoom and Teams is essential. This position reports to the Controller, but has a high degree of visibility and interaction with the CFO and other members of company leadership.
